r cargo binaries` — PASS\n\n## AC 3: Node.js project — Dockerfile includes Node.js 20 LTS, npm, Semgrep, showboat, claude-code\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\nEvidence from `src/lib/stacks/nodejs.ts` lines 328-336:\n- `nodesource/setup_20.x` (Node.js 20 LTS)\n- `npm install -g showboat @anthropic-ai/claude-code` (showboat, claude-code)\n- Semgrep installed in generator base: `pipx install semgrep && pipx ensurepath`\n\nTests:\n- `NodejsProvider.getVerifyDockerfileSection > returns Node.js 20 install via nodesource` — PASS\n- `NodejsProvider.getVerifyDockerfileSection > installs showboat and claude-code` — PASS\n- `generateVerifyDockerfile > includes Node.js section for nodejs stack` — PASS\n\n## AC 4: Python project — Dockerfile includes Python 3, pip, venv, Semgrep, verification tooling\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\nEvidence from `src/lib/stacks/python.ts` lines 242-249:\n- `python3-pip python3-venv` (pip, venv)\n- `coverage pytest` (verification tooling)\n- Semgrep from generator base layer\n\nTests:\n- `PythonProvider.getVerifyDockerfileSection > installs python3-pip and python3-venv` — PASS\n- `PythonProvider.getVerifyDockerfileSection > installs coverage and pytest` — PASS\n- `generateVerifyDockerfile > includes Python section for python stack` — PASS\n\n## AC 5: Rust project WITHOUT Bevy — Dockerfile includes toolchain but NOT Bevy system libs\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\nEvidence from `src/lib/stacks/rust.ts` lines 201-207: Bevy detection uses `hasCargoDep(depsSection, 'bevy')` — when false, `aptPackages` only contains `build-essential pkg-config libssl-dev`.\n\nTests:\n- `RustProvider.getVerifyDockerfileSection > does NOT include Bevy libs when bevy is not in dependencies` — PASS\n- `RustProvider.getVerifyDockerfileSection > does NOT include Bevy libs when no Cargo.toml exists` — PASS\n- `RustProvider.getVerifyDockerfileSection > does NOT include Bevy libs when bevy is only in dev-dependencies` — PASS\n- `generateVerifyDockerfile > does NOT include Bevy libs for rust project w